org.nerd4j.csv.field

Interface CSVFieldConverter<S,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - type of the source field format.
    T - type of the target field format.
    All Superinterfaces:
    CSVProcessOperation, CSVRegistryEntry
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCSVFieldConverter, BooleanToString, DateToString, EmptyCSVFieldConverter, EnumToString, NumberToString, StringToBoolean, StringToDate, StringToEnum, StringToNumber

    public interface CSVFieldConverter<S,T>
extends CSVProcessOperation, CSVRegistryEntry
    Represents a converter able to convert the CSV field in String into is object oriented representation and vice versa.
    Author:
    Nerd4j Team

      • convert

        T convert(S source,
          CSVFieldProcessContext context)
        Applies the conversion of the field in source format and returns the field in target format.

        If the conversion fails it modifies the context accordingly with the framework policies.

        Parameters:
        source - the CSV field to convert.
        context - the field process execution context.
        Returns:
        the CSV field in converted format.
